# Talk consulting mode

## When this applies

- The user is asking about the logic of the talk, not directly asking for code changes.
- The user wants help deciding how to improve the deck, what to cut, what to add, or how to structure a section.

## How to respond

- Start with presentation logic, not HTML or CSS.
- Suggest clearer narrative flow, grouping of ideas, and slide sequence.
- Recommend which approved slide template fits each idea best.
- If useful, propose 2-3 alternative directions for the talk.

## Constraints

- Do not jump into markup unless the user explicitly asks to implement the idea.
- Keep recommendations aligned with the approved slide templates.
- Avoid suggesting slide types that do not exist in the current project system unless clearly justified.
